3) Return a compact summary (limit 20 rows) of these relaxed segments with columns: cmdb_id, kpi_name, anomaly_type, start_ts, end_ts, length_minutes, max_value, min_value, global_P95, global_P05, severity. Sort by length_minutes desc then severity desc.
4) Also return two small aggregates: (a) total number of relaxed segments found, and (b) a per-component count of relaxed segments (top 10 components by count).
